post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Giving a legal framework to the use of certain drugs may help to prevent the development of infectious diseases.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A society where everyone consumes moderate amounts of drugs wouldn't be much different than the societies of today. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[A study](http://aic.gov.au/media_library/publications/tandi_pdf/tandi372.pdf) came to the conclusion that alcohol consumption was involved in 47% of homicides in Australia in a six-year period. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The prohibition forces users, that are otherwise law-abiding citizens, into transactions with more serious law-breakers, opening them up for the possibility to escalate to more serious crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There has been [no scientific consensus](https://newatlas.com/study-effects-ecstasy/10995/) on the long-term effects of ecstasy use.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Colorado has seen a "[slight increase](https://www.colorado.gov/pacific/cdphe/marijuana-use-2017)" in the number of adult marijuana users in the period 2014-2017 following legalisation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tracing the rapist after the rape does not undo the rape itself, as the harm was already done.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The responsible use of drugs for recreational purposes does not harm others and therefore can not be considered immoral. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to the [Global Commission on Drug Policy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Commission_on_Drug_Policy), the war on drugs was a failure. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Shooting galleries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supervised_injection_site) could be provided by the government as a safe environment for those requiring them. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prosecution takes place after the repercussions have occurred. A ban can prevent them from ever happening.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow governments to fight addictive drugs more effectively. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Albert Hofman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Albert_Hofmann), the creator of LSD, took LSD for over two decades without any health implications.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Banning drugs is akin to what happens in the film [Minority Report](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minority_Report_\\(film\\)): it's arresting people for what they might do under the influence. We could as soon prosecute people for being out of work, drinking, gambling or adultery."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations. At least the competition would seriously damage their overheads.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The risk of MDMA is not higher than many sports. MDMA has been compared to [horseback riding](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk/7876425.stm) in terms of risks. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [relatives](https://novarecoverycenter.com/drug-use/parental-drug-abuse/) of addicts are negatively impacted by their addiction. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "By legalizing and maintaining the produce of drugs for recreational use, the risk of users getting a hold of a drug falsely advertised for being something else when it's rather poisonous would never happen. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legal, health institutions can give people valuable information on how much you can take and other health advice on drugs. Now they can't because they would 'support' taking drugs and so also 'support' something illegal. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This isn't possible with the most popular date rape drug alcohol, at least not in higher doses, as it's taste is quite unmistakable."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs will likely make it a lot easier for young people to get access to them. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Knowledge that a friend or relative is using drugs can cause significant psychological stress to a caring or sensitive individual.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This is similar to how legal drugs, such as alcohol, are currently treated in most countries: harmful use is punished and use that does not harm others is not. This distinction allows those who use drugs safely to do so without repercussions. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would enable people to easily manage their own pain medication themselves without the trials and tribulations of doctors and presciptions and all those agonizing hoops you need to jump through along the way.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, obtaining such drugs is risky, restricted and requires work. Even if they're available, making them freely available may increase the number of rape incidents."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue is not drug legalization, but the functioning of the health insurances. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having the option to buy regulated drugs is surely better than only having the black market option. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a tautological argument, presupposing that prohibiting drugs is morally right.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't apply where there is no NHS or equivalent."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalising drugs would be damaging for public health. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Former inmates are significantly more at risk of drug-related mortality than the general population.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Established companies selling drugs could be just as dangerous \\(to society\\) as criminals.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Designer drugs already exist, are legal and work this angle. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Decriminalization would encourage the implementation of a broader scope of impairment detection devices. This would cause users to think twice about driving impaired on substances they believe wouldn't be detected using current methods. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A more substantial part of society will be exposed to the harmful and dangerous side effects of drugs.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug legalisation will make it easier to carry out [sexual assaults](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug-facilitated_sexual_assault).'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [global financial crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_crisis_of_2007%E2%80%932008) was caused by big companies acting with only their profits in mind, and the detrimental effects are still felt today. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Further studies on the "Rat Park" experiment discussed in the video [have found](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rat_Park#Reaction_to_the_experiment) social isolation is not necessary for addiction.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Laws should be introduced on an entirely pragmatic basis, not on the basis of moral signaling. If legalising drugs reduces harm, this should be sufficient evidence that it is a good policy. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Nearly all negative effects of addicts on their families are not fueled by the addiction itself, but the fact that the drug they are addicted to is made illegal by the ban on drugs. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Some adults may sell drugs to underaged people to make profit. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help law enforcement agencies.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not fair to solve such a problem by prohibiting heroin use for everyone. It should be solved as a problem on its own. This could mean anything from forbidding heroin addicts to have children \\(or parents to use heroin\\), to forming organisations for helping such families. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Removing support for someone mentally ill comes with costs. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of a drug means more education and informing for children in this matter. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Producers and distributors are not able to control how consumers use their products. Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Alcohol-dependent persons](https://academic.oup.com/alcalc/article/46/2/105/198339) have to face prejudices, although the substance is legal: They are often held responsible for their condition, are subject to social rejection and they are at particular risk for structural discrimination.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Organized crime would find themselves without a cash-flow and resort to much more violent kidnapping and extortion. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Established companies selling drugs could be just as dangerous \\(to society\\) as criminals.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The logic of this argument would necessitate prohibition of alcohol, along with cigarettes, prescription painkillers, household cleaning products, motor vehicles, power tools; and anything a person may use to end their life consciously or accidentally. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The evidence provided in this claim stems largely from importing cheaper cigarettes from the rest of Europe to the UK. The difference in quality is probably minimal. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Assuming that drugs will still be legally forbidden for people under a certain age, the distribution points will not be allowed to sell it to children.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, addicts would be forced to buy legally, meaning there is a record of their usage and authorities can intervene if there is an instance of drug abuse.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Regulated, corporate or government sale of these substances should not "target" low income areas and take advantage of disadvantaged people in the same way that current gangs, criminal organizations and other drug dealers currently do. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Driving a car or operating machinery while under the influence of drugs is illegal. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Prohibition clearly isn't enough either, and all but ensures that honest education and information becomes impossible, making it exaggerated and ineffective."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Shooting \\(illegally obtained\\) heroin is like playing Russian roulette every time: if a batch is too strong, over-dosing is likely. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs will help treat addicts. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is not the government's responsibility to provide a safe place for dangerous recreational activities. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Individuals who do not seek out dangerous activities shouldn't be punished for those who do. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, the potency of available alcoholic drinks grew significantly \\([pg. 3](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug users are detained along with violent criminals.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Criminals are not interested in drugs, their core interest is money. To gain the largest amount of money, in the quickest time, with the least effort, is their ultimate goal. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Ending the war on drugs will reduce [police casualties](https://www.vox.com/2014/10/29/7083371/swat-no-knock-raids-police-killed-civilians-dangerous-work-drugs). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While neither seems acceptable, most would rather face prejudice than prison. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Someone experiencing elevated stress levels isn't a good enough justification to limit other people's freedom by force. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegality of less addictive alternatives to legally prescribed opioids has been a large factor in the opioid crisis. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "An Indian based study shows that substance consumption highly relate to [juvenile delinquency.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4919962/) That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs such as PCP have caused [grotesque instances](https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/real-life-stories/rapper-killed-girlfriend-chewed-up-11566075) of violence by the user onto other individuals.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't necessarily mean drugs should be legalized. Alternatively, we could make alcohol, cigarettes and fast food illegal. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Numerous events have an equal impact on moral judgments; This should not be the reason for the ban on drug use. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This essentially places the onus of care back on the government to regulate to keep users safe. If the idea is the government should not control what we do with our bodies this proposition does not really make sense.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Both of these "contracts" are often initiated under desperate circumstances or by ill informed people.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Sleep deprivation](https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/03/070301081831.htm) negatively affects moral judgment and decision-making. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would enable people to easily manage their own pain medication themselves without the trials and tribulations of doctors and presciptions and all those agonizing hoops you need to jump through along the way.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs being illegal prevented addiction, there would be no drug addicted person. Thus, there is no prevention by just keeping drugs illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The evidence provided in this claim stems largely from importing cheaper cigarettes from the rest of Europe to the UK. The difference in quality is probably minimal. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The pharmaceutical industry is far less dangerous or violent than the alternative of drug cartels. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugging and raping someone is way more risky than buying illegal drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Professional addiction treatment is usually [expensive](https://www.addictioncenter.com/rehab-questions/cost-of-drug-and-alcohol-treatment/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations.
